for sharing his toys, you know?

40:24.091 --> 40:25.843
What the fuck was Cory thinking?

40:25.843 --> 40:28.846
That he would massively
upgrade his profile

40:28.846 --> 40:31.807
by getting into bed
with a fucking billionaire.

40:33.851 --> 40:36.395
He's using me as his honey trap.

40:36.395 --> 40:40.357
This fucker who couldn't wait to get rid
of me three years ago.

40:42.276 --> 40:44.027
Put in all this time, you know?

40:44.820 --> 40:49.533
Twenty years
and it just doesn't mean anything.

40:49.533 --> 40:51.869
- Doesn't mean a fucking thing.
- I know.

40:51.869 --> 40:57.040
We are only here to keep
the stockholders happy, and that is it.

40:57.040 --> 40:58.834
I'm so tired of being managed.

41:00.836 --> 41:03.589
You ask for things politely
like a grown-up,

41:03.589 --> 41:05.507
- and you just get nothing.
- Yep.

41:06.383 --> 41:10.095
Why do I have to set something on fire
to get someone to listen to me?

41:10.095 --> 41:11.889
'Cause Cory's a fucking pyromaniac,

41:11.889 --> 41:13.849
and that's
the only language he understands, and--

41:13.849 --> 41:17.394
I just didn't do all this
to become a corporate Stepford wife.

41:18.854 --> 41:19.855
God.

41:19.855 --> 41:21.857
Just fuck 'em.
You know what I mean? Fuck them.

41:21.857 --> 41:24.359
Fuck their rocket. Stupid f--

41:25.277 --> 41:27.988
- Fuck 'em.
- Seriously.

41:29.990 --> 41:31.033
Okay.

41:34.995 --> 41:36.038
Shit.

41:36.038 --> 41:37.706
What? Shit, what?

41:38.290 --> 41:39.583
It's Bradley.

41:41.084 --> 41:42.294
What? What is it?

41:42.961 --> 41:48.258
"Luna got arrested. Headed to Del Rio.
Can you spare a camera operator?"

41:49.134 --> 41:50.219
Shit.

41:54.056 --> 41:55.599
Wait, what?

42:03.857 --> 42:05.651
Earl, what is it?

42:05.651 --> 42:08.070
<i>Bradley Jackson is on her way to JFK.</i>

42:08.070 --> 42:11.114
<i>Told her team she won't be back
for tomorrow evening's broadcast.</i>

42:11.114 --> 42:12.574
<i>She's going to Texas.</i>

42:14.076 --> 42:15.369
Of course she is.

42:35.931 --> 42:37.182
Oh, God.

42:37.683 --> 42:40.769
Alex? It's Mia.

42:48.360 --> 42:49.903
Where is she?

42:49.903 --> 42:51.196
It's not personal.

42:51.196 --> 42:53.991
- She wants you to know that. Fuck me.
- Oh, my God.

43:16.305 --> 43:17.639
Alex is gone.

43:18.307 --> 43:19.766
How gone?

43:19.766 --> 43:21.977
The kind where I wake you up four hours

43:21.977 --> 43:24.521
before a rocket launch gone.

43:24.521 --> 43:26.064
- Can I blame you?
- What?

43:26.064 --> 43:28.609
No! She bailed on purpose.

43:29.568 --> 43:32.654
- Why?
- Does it matter? She's not here.

43:32.654 --> 43:33.906
- Okay.
- Okay?

43:33.906 --> 43:34.823
- Okay.
- Okay.

43:34.823 --> 43:38.911
So we need somebody
who can deliver the news in space.

43:38.911 --> 43:41.663
Yeah. I think it's gotta be Yanko.
He's a scientist. He would kill to go.

43:41.663 --> 43:44.416
No, no. It's Women's History Month.

43:45.250 --> 43:46.710
Our advertisers will freak.

43:48.086 --> 43:50.589
There really only is one option.

43:50.589 --> 43:52.174
It's an incredible opportunity.

43:52.174 --> 43:53.675
An Olympic champion in space.

43:53.675 --> 43:55.177
We're gonna turn it
into a regular segment.

43:55.177 --> 43:56.303
Educate our viewers on the science

43:56.303 --> 43:57.596
- of going into space.
- You said--

43:57.596 --> 43:59.389
You said you wanted
to get more girls into STEM.

43:59.389 --> 44:01.308
- For sure. Yeah.
- You said that.

44:01.308 --> 44:04.978
Paul Marks wants Alex.
So does everybody else. I haven't trained.

44:04.978 --> 44:08.148
- Oh, well. The training is bullshit.
- You don't need to train.

44:08.148 --> 44:10.234
You can do it. You're an Olympic champion.

44:10.234 --> 44:12.319
- I'm on three hours of sleep.
- So?

44:12.319 --> 44:14.363
You want me to get into a metal tube

44:14.363 --> 44:16.365
full of thousands of gallons
of rocket fuel

44:16.365 --> 44:18.242
on its first manned flight?

44:18.742 --> 44:20.452
- Well--
- Yeah.

44:20.452 --> 44:22.621
- Yes, but it's not--
- It's not that hard.

44:22.621 --> 44:24.623
I'm gonna pass on being your guinea pig.

44:24.623 --> 44:27.209
- Are you sure?
- See you at the launch.

44:30.879 --> 44:33.340
Huh. That went well.

44:33.340 --> 44:34.550
Now what?

44:39.596 --> 44:42.266
Hey, we have a problem.

44:43.308 --> 44:46.687
<i>Welcome to San Antonio
International Airport.</i>

44:55.904 --> 44:58.782
Cory. What are you doing here?

44:58.782 --> 45:01.243
- Well, we need to talk.
- No, I can't. I gotta go.

45:01.243 --> 45:03.036
- I got a source who's in trouble.
- Luna?

45:03.036 --> 45:04.746
- I know she's been arrested.
- What?

45:06.081 --> 45:07.708
Wait, are you trying to stop me?

45:07.708 --> 45:09.877
There's nothing
that you can do for her now.

45:09.877 --> 45:11.461
I've called Legal. They're on it, okay?

45:11.461 --> 45:13.088
Because y'all have been so supportive.

45:13.088 --> 45:16.175
Hey, I am not punishing you.

45:16.717 --> 45:20.804
I would never do that.
But I need you to do something for me.

45:22.097 --> 45:23.098
Okay.

45:23.098 --> 45:26.185
Hey. I was there for you, remember?

45:31.231 --> 45:33.317
I need you to return the favor.

45:44.828 --> 45:46.997
Yeah. Okay. What is it?

45:49.333 --> 45:51.877
Well, since you're in the neighborhood,

45:51.877 --> 45:53.504
wanna go to space?

45:54.505 --> 45:57.174
Oh, my God.
I can't believe he got you to do this.

45:57.674 --> 45:59.051
I really-- I can't believe it.

45:59.051 --> 46:00.886
How are you not coming?
This is your story.

46:00.886 --> 46:03.263
<i>You have been chasing this story, Bradley.</i>

46:03.263 --> 46:06.934
Well, it's your story now,
so shoot the shit out of it, okay?

46:07.518 --> 46:09.520
And tell Luna I'm sorry.

46:10.229 --> 46:13.232
And if it all goes south,
you can have my dressing room.

46:13.232 --> 46:15.108
Well, what about your apartment?

46:16.193 --> 46:17.694
You mean the one you haven't even seen?

46:19.029 --> 46:21.823
Oh, God. Please,
you know you don't have to do this, right?

46:23.784 --> 46:26.161
I know. It's-- But it's like you said.

46:26.161 --> 46:28.580
Maybe I don't have to fight every battle.

46:30.290 --> 46:33.377
Please just be safe. God, please be safe.

46:33.377 --> 46:34.837
<i>Okay. Bye.</i>

46:43.929 --> 46:46.014
So, folks,
we have a last-minute change of plans.

46:46.014 --> 46:48.809
We've just learned that Alex
unfortunately suffered a minor injury

46:48.809 --> 46:50.477
while she was training
earlier this morning.

46:50.477 --> 46:52.396
So out of an abundance
of caution,

46:52.396 --> 46:55.691
our <i>Evening News</i> anchor Bradley Jackson,
she's gonna be going in her place.

46:55.691 --> 46:59.111
And Alex is fine.
She just felt it best to step aside.

46:59.111 --> 47:00.529
<i>That's right.
Despite the quick change of plans...</i>

47:00.529 --> 47:01.655
Go quickly to camera three.

47:01.655 --> 47:04.449
<i>...Bradley was actually able to complete
that training pretty quickly,</i>

47:04.449 --> 47:05.576
<i>so she's good to go.</i>

47:05.576 --> 47:08.287
And I'm thrilled to be here
with you in beautiful West Texas.

47:08.287 --> 47:10.581
- Look at this big, blue, Lone Star sky.
- Yeah.

47:10.581 --> 47:13.083
And I can only imagine how incredibly
excited Bradley must be.

47:13.083 --> 47:16.461
I know she is insanely excited.

47:26.471 --> 47:29.183
My body, my choice. My body, my choice.

47:29.183 --> 47:33.228
I'm here in Del Rio, Texas,
a small city on the US-Mexico border,

47:33.228 --> 47:36.690
where a 19-year-old woman
is being held in this building

47:36.690 --> 47:38.817
since she was arrested late yesterday.

47:39.318 --> 47:41.320
- She is part--
- Back it up. You need to clear the area.

47:41.320 --> 47:43.864
She is part of an underground network
of volunteers

47:43.864 --> 47:46.992
who have been bringing abortion pills
from Mexico into the US.

47:46.992 --> 47:50.078
Medication abortion is safe,
and it is effective,

47:50.078 --> 47:53.874
and here in the remote Rio Grande Valley
often the only option.

47:57.920 --> 48:02.508
Well, congratulations, Paul.
This is Bradley Jackson.

48:02.508 --> 48:06.053
You just got yourself a whole new set
of viewers south of the Mason-Dixon line.

48:06.053 --> 48:08.388
Well, thanks for the ride.
I'm gonna try not to throw up.

48:08.388 --> 48:10.265
Well, there's a bag underneath your seat.

48:10.265 --> 48:11.892
Just make sure you seal it.

48:21.985 --> 48:25.781
Cory Ellison, boy wonder.
Looks like you can't deliver after all.

49:00.399 --> 49:02.025
<i>SNA arm rotation enabled.</i>

49:02.025 --> 49:03.944
<i>Stage one tanks pressing for flight.</i>

49:03.944 --> 49:05.195
Take camera five.

49:06.655 --> 49:08.782
<i>GLS mainline has been initiated.</i>

49:08.782 --> 49:11.118
<i>All personnel,
we are going to resume the clock.</i>

49:12.703 --> 49:13.787
All right.

49:13.787 --> 49:18.542
The G's can be a little intense, but
it's only for the first couple of minutes.

49:18.542 --> 49:20.919
This is nothing.
I used to fly Spirit Airlines.

49:22.921 --> 49:24.715
<i>T-minus 15 seconds.</i>

49:26.466 --> 49:27.718
Standby to launch.

49:27.718 --> 49:29.428
- <i>Ten, nine...</i>
- Ten, nine...

49:29.428 --> 49:34.808
<i>...eight, seven, six, five, four, three...</i>

49:35.392 --> 49:36.935
- <i>two, one.</i>
- Two, one!

