Hyperion One <i>has cleared the tower.</i>

49:47.988 --> 49:50.782
- <i>You can feel the ground shaking.</i>
- Keep it.

49:59.249 --> 50:02.085
That is absolutely incredible.
The power of this thing--

50:02.085 --> 50:04.630
It takes a lot of juice
to punch a hole in that sky.

50:04.630 --> 50:06.089
We'll be seeing footage

50:06.089 --> 50:08.634
- <i>of Earth from the rocket itself.</i>
- Stay with it, five. Stay with it.

50:08.634 --> 50:13.430
Hyperion One <i>will reach a top speed
of 2,250 miles an hour.</i>

50:13.430 --> 50:14.890
<i>It's impressive, Chris.</i>

50:14.890 --> 50:18.435
<i>That's right.
And reach an apogee of about 350,000 feet,</i>

50:18.435 --> 50:20.521
<i>which is about 62 miles
above the Earth's surface.</i>

50:25.234 --> 50:28.195
So <i>Hyperion One</i> is now
closing in on the Kármán Line.

50:28.195 --> 50:30.989
